# Git commits in Evoke

When committing or drafting commit messages for this repo:

1. Subject: `feat:` / `fix:` / `bugfix:` + one-line imperative summary
2. Body: **bullet list only** (`- ` per line). Never use prose paragraphs in the body.
<!-- 3. Do not add `Co-authored-by: Cursor` or other trailers -->
4. Read `.cursor/skills/evoke-git-commits/SKILL.md` before any commit the user requests

Example body:

```
- Add X for Y
- Fix Z when W happens
```
